  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best books for the self preparation of EE GATE?",
  "response": "Preparing for the Electrical Engineering (EE) GATE exam requires a combination of understanding fundamental concepts and practicing problem-solving. Here are some highly recommended books that can help you prepare effectively:\n\n### Core Subjects:\n1. **Network Theory**\n   - \"Engineering Circuit Analysis\" by William H. Hayt and Jack E. Kemmerly\n   - \"Electric Circuits\" by James W. Nilsson and Susan Riedel\n\n2. **Signals and Systems**\n   - \"Signals and Systems\" by Alan V. Oppenheim, Alan S. Willsky, and S. Hamid Nawab\n   - \"Principles of Linear Systems and Signals\" by B.P. Lathi\n\n3. **Control Systems**\n   - \"Automatic Control Systems\" by Benjamin C. Kuo\n   - \"Modern Control Engineering\" by Katsuhiko Ogata\n\n4. **Electromagnetics**\n   - \"Engineering Electromagnetics\" by William H. Hayt\n   - \"Electromagnetics\" by John D. Kraus\n\n5. **Power Systems**\n   - \"Power System Engineering\" by D.P. Kothari and I.J. Nagrath\n   - \"Electrical Power Systems\" by C.L. Wadhwa\n\n6. **Electrical Machines**\n   - \"Electrical Machinery\" by P.S. Bimbhra\n   - \"The Performance and Design of Alternating Current Machines\" by M.G. Say\n\n7. **Power Electronics**\n   - \"Power Electronics: Converters, Applications, and Design\" by Ned Mohan, Tore M. Undeland, and William P. Robbins\n   - \"Power Electronics: Circuits, Devices & Applications\" by Muhammad H. Rashid\n\n### Mathematics:\n1. **Engineering Mathematics**\n   - \"Higher Engineering Mathematics\" by B.S. Grewal\n   - \"Advanced Engineering Mathematics\" by Erwin Kreyszig\n\n### General Aptitude:\n1. **Verbal Ability & Analytical Reasoning**\n   - \"A Modern Approach to Verbal & Non-Verbal Reasoning\" by R.S. Aggarwal\n\n### Solved Papers and Practice:\n1. **Previous Years' Question Papers**\n   - \"GATE Guide Electrical Engineering\" by GKP\n   - \"GATE Electrical Engineering Solved Papers\" by Made Easy Editorial Board\n\n### Online Resources:\n- Websites like NPTEL offer free video lectures by IIT professors, which can be very helpful for understanding complex topics.\n\n### Strategy:\n1. **Understand the Syllabus**: Begin by thoroughly understanding the GATE syllabus for EE.\n2. **Stick to Standard Textbooks**: Use the recommended standard textbooks for building your concepts.\n3. **Practice Regularly**: Solving previous years' papers and taking mock tests is crucial.\n4. **Join Study Groups**: Participating in study groups can facilitate knowledge sharing and problem-solving.\n\nBy combining these resources with a well-structured study plan, you can prepare effectively for the GATE EE exam. Good luck!",
